result.execSummary:
The defendant Jennifer M Wojtalewicz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jennifer M Wojtalewicz in court with attorney D. Nicholas Carroll. Michael Daniel Zell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases heard at this time are 15CM-103, 15CM-215, 15CM-280, 15CM-526, 15CM-527, 17CM-123, 17CM-136, 18CM-15 and 18CM-23.

9:05 AM Court calls cases.
Atty Zell states appearances.

Matter was set for a trial today, there is a plea agreement now. Defendant will enter pleas into three counts this morning.

Cases being dismissed and read in: 15CM-215, 15CM-526, 15CM-280, 17CM-123, 17CM-136 and 18CM-23.
15CM-103: Defendant will enter a plea to Count 2. Count 1 will be dismissed and read in
15CM-527: Defendant will enter a plea to Count 2. Remaining counts will be dismissed and read in
18CM-15: Defendant will enter a plea to Count 1. Count 2 will be dismissed and read in

Atty Carroll concurs.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.
Defendant read plea questionnaire before signing it.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
15CM-103: Count 2: NO CONTEST
15CM-527: Count 2: NO CONTEST
18CM-15: Count 1: NO CONTEST

Court questions Defendant regarding pleas.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney Carroll for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charges.

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.
Court finds the defendant guilty.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
15CM-103: Count 1: Dismissed and read in
15CM-103: Count 2: Disorderly Conduct
15CM-527: Count 1: Dismissed and read in
15CM-527: Count 2: Disorderly Conduct
15CM-527: Count 3: Dismissed and read in
15CM-527: Count 4: Dismissed and read in
15CM-527: Count 5: Dismissed and read in
18CM-15: Count 1: Resisting/Obstructing an Officer
18CM-15: Count 2: Dismissed and read in
Dismissed and read in: 15CM-215, 15CM-526, 15CM-280, 17CM-123, 17CM-136 and 18CM-23

Atty Zell makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
State has complied with victim notification statutes. There is no victim impact statement and there was no request to speak today.

Atty Carroll makes sentencing arguments to the Court, this is a joint recommendation.
Defendant addresses the Court prior to sentencing.

Court has a number of factors to consider to determine sentencing.

BY THE COURT:
15CM-103:
Count 2:
Jail sentence for 60 days
60 days jail credit
Pay costs and assessments
60 days to pay or set up a payment plan 

15CM-527: 
Count 2:
Jail sentence for 60 days, imposed and stayed
8 days jail credit if revoked
Probation for a period of 12 months
Conditions:
Obtain AODA Assessment and comply with any recommendations from the treatment
Abstain from use of illegal controlled substances without a valid prescription 
Provide authorization for release of medication records so agent can keep informed
Comply with any recommendations agent may have for a treatment or counseling
Early discharge from probation if there are no prior violations of terms of probation and if agent recommends
Pay costs 

18CM-15:
Count 1: 
Jail sentence for 60 days, imposed and stayed, concurrent to 15CM-527
8 days jail credit if revoked
Probation for a period of 12 months, concurrent to 15CM-527
Conditions:
Comply with conditions as stated in 15CM-527
Pay costs
